<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="L" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Lock2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Lock,</orth> subst. an instrument to fasten doors or chests: <bibl n="shak. ven 575" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 575</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. luc 302" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 302</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 1.2.35" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. I, 2, 35</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 1.2.176" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 I, 2, 176</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 3.1.138" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. III, 1, 138</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 4.1.46" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. IV, 1, 46</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 4.2.22" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. IV, 2, 22</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 3.2.36" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 2, 36</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.4.1" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 4, 1</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.4.1" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 4, 1</bibl> Metaphorically: <cit><quote>defile the --s of your shrill-shrieking daughters,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 3.3.35" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 3, 35</bibl></cit> (or == curls?); cf. <cit><quote>I have picked the l. and ta'en the treasure of her honour,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 2.2.41" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. II, 2, 41</bibl></cit>.
